The paper deals with the problem of detecting and localizing image manipulations, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The proposed method uses deep learning techniques, which are also commonly used in computer vision and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a surrogate task for training the model, which is a common approach in information retrieval (cs.IR) research. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of image forensics, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR).
